{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1936,"text":"Can we, as adults, grow new nerve cells?"},{"time":7150,"text":"There's still some confusion\nabout that question,"},{"time":10261,"text":"as this is a fairly new field of research."},{"time":13569,"text":"For example, I was talking\nto one of my colleagues, Robert,"},{"time":16952,"text":"who is an oncologist,"},{"time":18284,"text":"and he was telling me,"},{"time":20014,"text":"\"Sandrine, this is puzzling."},{"time":21793,"text":"Some of my patients that have been told\nthey are cured of their cancer"},{"time":26131,"text":"still develop symptoms of depression.\""},{"time":29520,"text":"And I responded to him,"},{"time":30839,"text":"\"Well, from my point of view\nthat makes sense."},{"time":33203,"text":"The drug you give to your patients\nthat stops the cancer cells multiplying"},{"time":37765,"text":"also stops the newborn neurons\nbeing generated in their brain.\""},{"time":43820,"text":"And then Robert looked at me\nlike I was crazy and said,"},{"time":46630,"text":"\"But Sandrine, these are adult patients --"},{"time":48836,"text":"adults do not grow new nerve cells.\""},{"time":52543,"text":"And much to his surprise, I said,\n\"Well actually, we do.\""},{"time":57098,"text":"And this is a phenomenon\nthat we call neurogenesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61948,"text":"[Neurogenesis]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63162,"text":"Now Robert is not a neuroscientist,"},{"time":66956,"text":"and when he went to medical school\nhe was not taught what we know now --"},{"time":71605,"text":"that the adult brain\ncan generate new nerve cells."},{"time":77217,"text":"So Robert, you know,\nbeing the good doctor that he is,"},{"time":81611,"text":"wanted to come to my lab"},{"time":83334,"text":"to understand the topic\na little bit better."},{"time":86881,"text":"And I took him for a tour"},{"time":89160,"text":"of one of the most exciting\nparts of the brain"},{"time":92097,"text":"when it comes to neurogenesis --"},{"time":94294,"text":"and this is the hippocampus."},{"time":97080,"text":"So this is this gray structure\nin the center of the brain."},{"time":101613,"text":"And what we've known already\nfor very long,"},{"time":104059,"text":"is that this is important for learning,\nmemory, mood and emotion."},{"time":109343,"text":"However, what we\nhave learned more recently"},{"time":112414,"text":"is that this is one of the unique\nstructures of the adult brain"},{"time":117096,"text":"where new neurons can be generated."},{"time":120405,"text":"And if we slice through the hippocampus"},{"time":122740,"text":"and zoom in,"},{"time":124032,"text":"what you actually see here in blue"},{"time":126857,"text":"is a newborn neuron\nin an adult mouse brain."},{"time":132769,"text":"So when it comes to the human brain --"},{"time":135848,"text":"my colleague Jonas Fris√©n\nfrom the Karolinska Institutet,"},{"time":139404,"text":"has estimated that we produce\n700 new neurons per day"},{"time":145168,"text":"in the hippocampus."},{"time":147183,"text":"You might think this is not much,"},{"time":148882,"text":"compared to the billions\nof neurons we have."},{"time":151644,"text":"But by the time we turn 50,"},{"time":154739,"text":"we will have all exchanged the neurons\nwe were born with in that structure"},{"time":159439,"text":"with adult-born neurons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163248,"text":"So why are these new neurons important\nand what are their functions?"},{"time":169324,"text":"First, we know that they're important\nfor learning and memory."},{"time":173046,"text":"And in the lab we have shown"},{"time":174587,"text":"that if we block the ability\nof the adult brain"},{"time":177847,"text":"to produce new neurons in the hippocampus,"},{"time":180431,"text":"then we block certain memory abilities."},{"time":183721,"text":"And this is especially new and true\nfor spatial recognition --"},{"time":190657,"text":"so like, how you navigate\nyour way in the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194181,"text":"We are still learning a lot,"},{"time":195683,"text":"and neurons are not only important\nfor memory capacity,"},{"time":198770,"text":"but also for the quality of the memory."},{"time":201697,"text":"And they will have been helpful\nto add time to our memory"},{"time":205766,"text":"and they will help differentiate\nvery similar memories, like:"},{"time":210472,"text":"how do you find your bike"},{"time":212576,"text":"that you park at the station\nevery day in the same area,"},{"time":216116,"text":"but in a slightly different position?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220068,"text":"And more interesting\nto my colleague Robert"},{"time":222576,"text":"is the research we have been doing\non neurogenesis and depression."},{"time":228010,"text":"So in an animal model of depression,"},{"time":229972,"text":"we have seen that we have\na lower level of neurogenesis."},{"time":234500,"text":"And if we give antidepressants,"},{"time":236767,"text":"then we increase the production\nof these newborn neurons,"},{"time":240245,"text":"and we decrease\nthe symptoms of depression,"},{"time":243412,"text":"establishing a clear link\nbetween neurogenesis and depression."},{"time":249191,"text":"But moreover, if you\njust block neurogenesis,"},{"time":253524,"text":"then you block the efficacy\nof the antidepressant."},{"time":257714,"text":"So by then, Robert had understood"},{"time":259501,"text":"that very likely his patients\nwere suffering from depression"},{"time":263223,"text":"even after being cured of their cancer,"},{"time":265842,"text":"because the cancer drug had stopped\nnewborn neurons from being generated."},{"time":270247,"text":"And it will take time\nto generate new neurons"},{"time":273899,"text":"that reach normal functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277780,"text":"So, collectively, now we think\nwe have enough evidence"},{"time":282213,"text":"to say that neurogenesis\nis a target of choice"},{"time":285952,"text":"if we want to improve\nmemory formation or mood,"},{"time":289590,"text":"or even prevent the decline\nassociated with aging,"},{"time":293177,"text":"or associated with stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296288,"text":"So the next question is:"},{"time":298043,"text":"can we control neurogenesis?"},{"time":301066,"text":"The answer is yes."},{"time":302860,"text":"And we are now going to do a little quiz."},{"time":306201,"text":"I'm going to give you a set\nof behaviors and activities,"},{"time":309406,"text":"and you tell me if you think\nthey will increase neurogenesis"},{"time":314114,"text":"or if they will decrease neurogenesis."},{"time":316804,"text":"Are we ready?"},{"time":318550,"text":"OK, let's go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320034,"text":"So what about learning?"},{"time":322521,"text":"Increasing?"},{"time":323725,"text":"Yes."},{"time":324908,"text":"Learning will increase the production\nof these new neurons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328718,"text":"How about stress?"},{"time":331431,"text":"Yes, stress will decrease the production\nof new neurons in the hippocampus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336192,"text":"How about sleep deprivation?"},{"time":339375,"text":"Indeed, it will decrease neurogenesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342098,"text":"How about sex?"},{"time":344414,"text":"Oh, wow!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345590,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346881,"text":"Yes, you are right, it will increase\nthe production of new neurons."},{"time":350658,"text":"However, it's all about balance here."},{"time":352834,"text":"We don't want to fall in a situation --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355071,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":357023,"text":"about too much sex\nleading to sleep deprivation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359881,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362753,"text":"How about getting older?"},{"time":367645,"text":"So the neurogenesis rate\nwill decrease as we get older,"},{"time":371352,"text":"but it is still occurring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374042,"text":"And then finally, how about running?"},{"time":377912,"text":"I will let you judge that one by yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381563,"text":"So this is one of the first studies"},{"time":383383,"text":"that was carried out by one of my mentors,\nRusty Gage from the Salk Institute,"},{"time":387810,"text":"showing that the environment\ncan have an impact"},{"time":390108,"text":"on the production of new neurons."},{"time":392021,"text":"And here you see a section\nof the hippocampus of a mouse"},{"time":396299,"text":"that had no running wheel in its cage."},{"time":398568,"text":"And the little black dots you see\nare actually newborn neurons-to-be."},{"time":403246,"text":"And now, you see a section\nof the hippocampus of a mouse"},{"time":408408,"text":"that had a running wheel in its cage."},{"time":411028,"text":"So you see the massive increase"},{"time":412575,"text":"of the black dots representing\nthe new neurons-to-be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416819,"text":"So activity impacts neurogenesis,\nbut that's not all."},{"time":421639,"text":"What you eat will have an effect"},{"time":424310,"text":"on the production of new neurons\nin the hippocampus."},{"time":427248,"text":"So here we have a sample of diet --"},{"time":430232,"text":"of nutrients that have been shown\nto have efficacy."},{"time":433973,"text":"And I'm just going\nto point a few out to you:"},{"time":436592,"text":"Calorie restriction of 20 to 30 percent\nwill increase neurogenesis."},{"time":442128,"text":"Intermittent fasting --\nspacing the time between your meals --"},{"time":445634,"text":"will increase neurogenesis."},{"time":447797,"text":"Intake of flavonoids,"},{"time":449144,"text":"which are contained\nin dark chocolate or blueberries,"},{"time":452171,"text":"will increase neurogenesis."},{"time":454355,"text":"Omega-3 fatty acids,"},{"time":455885,"text":"present in fatty fish, like salmon,"},{"time":458120,"text":"will increase the production\nof these new neurons."},{"time":461502,"text":"Conversely, a diet rich\nin high saturated fat"},{"time":465627,"text":"will have a negative impact\non neurogenesis."},{"time":469232,"text":"Ethanol -- intake of alcohol --\nwill decrease neurogenesis."},{"time":473981,"text":"However, not everything is lost;"},{"time":476727,"text":"resveratrol, which is\ncontained in red wine,"},{"time":479803,"text":"has been shown to promote\nthe survival of these new neurons."},{"time":483708,"text":"So next time you are at a dinner party,"},{"time":485598,"text":"you might want to reach for this possibly\n\"neurogenesis-neutral\" drink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489909,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":492066,"text":"And then finally,\nlet me point out the last one --"},{"time":494591,"text":"a quirky one."},{"time":495773,"text":"So Japanese groups are fascinated\nwith food textures,"},{"time":499692,"text":"and they have shown that actually\nsoft diet impairs neurogenesis,"},{"time":505019,"text":"as opposed to food that requires\nmastication -- chewing -- or crunchy food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510827,"text":"So all of this data,"},{"time":512644,"text":"where we need to look\nat the cellular level,"},{"time":515249,"text":"has been generated using animal models."},{"time":518470,"text":"But this diet has also been given\nto human participants,"},{"time":522875,"text":"and what we could see is that\nthe diet modulates memory and mood"},{"time":529057,"text":"in the same direction\nas it modulates neurogenesis,"},{"time":532565,"text":"such as: calorie restriction\nwill improve memory capacity,"},{"time":537346,"text":"whereas a high-fat diet will exacerbate\nsymptoms of depression --"},{"time":542469,"text":"as opposed to omega-3 fatty acids,\nwhich increase neurogenesis,"},{"time":546357,"text":"and also help to decrease\nthe symptoms of depression."},{"time":551643,"text":"So we think that the effect of diet"},{"time":556484,"text":"on mental health, on memory and mood,"},{"time":560103,"text":"is actually mediated by the production\nof the new neurons in the hippocampus."},{"time":564994,"text":"And it's not only what you eat,"},{"time":566938,"text":"but it's also the texture\nof the food, when you eat it"},{"time":570027,"text":"and how much of it you eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573841,"text":"On our side -- neuroscientists\ninterested in neurogenesis --"},{"time":577898,"text":"we need to understand better\nthe function of these new neurons,"},{"time":581587,"text":"and how we can control their survival\nand their production."},{"time":585896,"text":"We also need to find a way to protect\nthe neurogenesis of Robert's patients."},{"time":591271,"text":"And on your side --"},{"time":592672,"text":"I leave you in charge\nof your neurogenesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595691,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596873,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602856,"text":"Margaret Heffernan:\nFantastic research, Sandrine."},{"time":605212,"text":"Now, I told you you changed my life --"},{"time":607481,"text":"I now eat a lot of blueberries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609283,"text":"Sandrine Thuret: Very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611528,"text":"MH: I'm really interested\nin the running thing."},{"time":614869,"text":"Do I have to run?"},{"time":617368,"text":"Or is it really just\nabout aerobic exercise,"},{"time":620034,"text":"getting oxygen to the brain?"},{"time":621663,"text":"Could it be any kind of vigorous exercise?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":624101,"text":"ST: So for the moment,"},{"time":625862,"text":"we can't really say\nif it's just the running itself,"},{"time":629126,"text":"but we think that anything that indeed\nwill increase the production --"},{"time":634187,"text":"or moving the blood flow to the brain,"},{"time":637291,"text":"should be beneficial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639353,"text":"MH: So I don't have to get\na running wheel in my office?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642004,"text":"ST: No, you don't!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643191,"text":"MH: Oh, what a relief! That's wonderful."},{"time":645308,"text":"Sandrine Thuret, thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647085,"text":"ST: Thank you, Margaret."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648308,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}